      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُهُ عَنِ اَلْعَارِيَّةِ يَسْتَعِيرُهَا اَلْإِنْسَانُ فَتَهْلِكُ أَوْ تُسْرَقُ فَقَالَ \"إِذَا كَانَ أَمِيناً فَلاَ غُرْمَ عَلَيْهِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4084 - Aban narrated from Muhammad ibn Muslim, from Abu Ja'far Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), who said:\nI asked him about a borrowed item (ariyyah) that a person borrows, and it either perishes or is stolen.\nImam (as) said: \"If he is trustworthy, then there is no liability upon him.\""
        ]
      }
